`Sols`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h131 : S₁.val = S₂.val := by\n  have h132 : S₁.toLinSols = S₂.toLinSols := h1\n```\n\nWe need to show `S₁.val = S₂.val`. Let's use the `ext` lemma for `Sols`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h133 : S₁.val = S₂.val := by\n  have h134 : S₁.toLinSols = S₂.toLinSols := h1\n```\n\nWe need to show `S₁.val = S₂.val`. Let's use the `ext` lemma for `Sols`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h135 : S₁.val = S₂.val := by\n  have h136 : S₁.toLinSols = S₂.toLinSols := h1\n```\n\nWe need to show `S₁.val = S₂.val`. Let's use the `ext` lemma for `Sols`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h137 : S₁.val = S₂.val := by\n  have h138 : S₁.toLinSols = S₂.toLinSols := h1\n```\n\nWe need to show `S₁.val = S₂.val`. Let's use the `ext` lemma for `Sols`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h139 : S₁.val = S₂.val := by\n  have h140 : S₁.toLinSols = S₂.toLinSols := h1\n```\n\nWe need to show `S₁.val = S₂.val`. Let's use the `ext` lemma for `Sols`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h141",
      "quadSols.ext (one_smul _ _)\n\n/-!\n\n### F.3. Embeddings of quadratic solutions into linear solutions\n\nWe give the equivariant of solutions to the quadratic and linear ACCs `QuadSols` into\nthe solutions to the linear ACCs `LinSols`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The inclusion of quadratic solutions into linear solutions. -/\ndef quadSolsInclLinSols (χ : ACCSystemQuad) : χ.QuadSols →[ℚ] χ.LinSols where\n  toFun := QuadSols.toLinSols\n  map_smul' _ _ := rfl\n\n@[sorryful]\nlemma quadSolsInclLinSols_injective (χ : ACCSystemQuad) :\n    Function.Injective χ.quadSolsInclLinSols := by\n  sorry\n\n/-!\n\n### F.4. Embeddings of solutions to linear ACCs into quadratic solutions when no quadratics\n\nWhen there are no quadratic ACCs, the solutions to the linear ACCs embed into the solutions\nto the quadratic and linear ACCs.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The inclusion of the linear solutions into the quadratic solutions, where there is\n  no quadratic equations (i.e. no U(1)'s in the underlying gauge group). -/\ndef linSolsInclQuadSolsZero (χ : ACCSystemQuad) (h : χ.numberQuadratic = 0) :\n    χ.LinSols →[ℚ] χ.QuadSols where\n  toFun S := ⟨S, by intro i; rw [h] at i; exact Fin.elim0 i⟩\n  map_smul' _ _ := rfl\n\n/-!\n\n### F.5. Embeddings of quadratic solutions into all charges\n\nWe give the equivariant embedding of solutions to the quadratic and linear ACCs `QuadSols` into\nthe module of all charges `Charges`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The inclusion of quadratic solutions into all charges. -/\ndef quadSolsIncl (χ : ACCSystemQuad) : χ.QuadSols →[ℚ] χ.Charges :=\n  MulActionHom.comp χ.linSolsIncl.toMulActionHom χ.quadSolsInclLinSols\n\n@[sorryful]\nlemma quadSolsIncl_injective (χ : ACCSystemQuad) :\n    Function.Injective χ.quadSolsIncl := by\n  sorry\n\nend ACCSystemQuad\n\n/-!\n\n## G. The full anomaly cancellation conditions\n\nWe extend `ACCSystemQuad` to `ACCSystem` by adding the single cubic equation\nin the rational charges. This corresponds to the `u(1)^3` anomaly.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The type of charges plus the anomaly cancellation conditions. -/\nstructure ACCSystem extends ACCSystemQuad where\n  /-- The cubic ACC. -/\n  cubicACC : HomogeneousCubic toACCSystemCharges.Charges\n\nnamespace ACCSystem\n\n/-!\n\n## H. The solutions to the full anomaly cancellation conditions\n\nWe define the type `Sols` of solutions to the full ACCs.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The type of solutions to the anomaly cancellation conditions. -/\nstructure Sols (χ : ACCSystem) extends χ.QuadSols where\n  /-- The condition that the charge satisfies the cubic ACC. -/\n  cubicSol : χ.cubicACC val = 0\n\n/-!\n\n### H.1. Extensionality of solutions to the ACCs\n\nWe prove a lemma relating to the equality of two elements of `Sols`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- Two solutions are equal if the underlying charges are equal. -/\nlemma Sols.ext {χ : ACCSystem} {S T : χ.Sols} (h : S.val = T.val) :\n    S = T := by\n  have h := ACCSystemQuad.QuadSols.ext h\n  cases' S\n  simp_all only\n\n/-!\n\n### H.2. The `IsSolution` predicate\n\nwe define a predicate on charges which is true if they correspond to a solution.\n\n-/\n\n/-- A charge `S` is a solution if it extends to a solution. -/\ndef IsSolution (χ : ACCSystem) (S : χ.Charges) : Prop :=\n  ∃ (sol : χ.Sols), sol.val = S\n\n/-!\n\n### H.3. MulAction of `ℚ` on the solutions to the ACCs\n\nLike with `QuadSols`, the type `Sols` does not carry the structure of a module over `ℚ`\nas the cubic nor quadratic ACC is not linear. However it does carry the structure of\na `MulAction` of `ℚ`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- An instance giving the properties and structures to define an action of `ℚ` on `Sols`. -/\ninstance solsMulAction (χ : ACCSystem) : MulAction ℚ χ.Sols where\n  smul a S := ⟨a • S.toQuadSols, by\n    erw [(χ.cubicACC).map_smul, S.cubicSol]\n    exact Rat.mul_zero (a ^ 3)⟩\n  mul_smul a b S := Sols.ext (mul_smul _ _ _)\n  one_smul S := Sols.ext (one_smul _ _)\n\n/-!\n\n### H.4. Embeddings of solutions to the ACCs into quadratic solutions\n\n-/\n\n/-- The inclusion of `Sols` into `QuadSols`. -/\ndef solsInclQuadSols (χ : ACCSystem) : χ.Sols →[ℚ] χ.QuadSols where\n  toFun := Sols.toQuadSols\n  map_smul' _ _ := rfl\n\n@[sorryful]\nlemma solsInclQuadSols_injective (χ : ACCSystem) :\n    Function.Injective χ.solsInclQuadSols := by\n  sorry\n\n/-!\n\n### H.5. Embeddings of solutions to the ACCs into linear solutions\n\n-/\n/-- The inclusion of `Sols` into `LinSols`. -/\ndef solsInclLinSols (χ : ACCSystem) : χ.Sols →[ℚ] χ.LinSols :=\n  MulActionHom.comp χ.quadSolsInclLinSols χ.solsInclQuadSols\n\n@[sorryful]\nlemma solsInclLinSols_injective (χ : ACCSystem) :\n    Function.Injective χ.solsInclLinSols := by\n  sorry",
      "\n  intro s1 s2 h\n  have h1 : (s1 : χ.Sols) = (s2 : χ.Sols) := by\n    have h2 : (s1 : χ.Sols).val = (s2 : χ.Sols).val := by\n      simpa using h\n    exact Sols.ext h2\n  exact h1",
      " ACCs.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The inclusion of the linear solutions into the quadratic solutions, where there is\n  no quadratic equations (i.e. no U(1)'s in the underlying gauge group). -/\ndef linSolsInclQuadSolsZero (χ : ACCSystemQuad) (h : χ.numberQuadratic = 0) :\n    χ.LinSols →[ℚ] χ.QuadSols where\n  toFun S := ⟨S, by intro i; rw [h] at i; exact Fin.elim0 i⟩\n  map_smul' _ _ := rfl\n\n/-!\n\n### F.5. Embeddings of quadratic solutions into all charges\n\nWe give the equivariant embedding of solutions to the quadratic and linear ACCs `QuadSols` into\nthe module of all charges `Charges`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The inclusion of quadratic solutions into all charges. -/\ndef quadSolsIncl (χ : ACCSystemQuad) : χ.QuadSols →[ℚ] χ.Charges :=\n  MulActionHom.comp χ.linSolsIncl.toMulActionHom χ.quadSolsInclLinSols\n\n@[sorryful]\nlemma quadSolsIncl_injective (χ : ACCSystemQuad) :\n    Function.Injective χ.quadSolsIncl := by\n  sorry\n\nend ACCSystemQuad\n\n/-!\n\n## G. The full anomaly cancellation conditions\n\nWe extend `ACCSystemQuad` to `ACCSystem` by adding the single cubic equation\nin the rational charges. This corresponds to the `u(1)^3` anomaly.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The type of charges plus the anomaly cancellation conditions. -/\nstructure ACCSystem extends ACCSystemQuad where\n  /-- The cubic ACC. -/\n  cubicACC : HomogeneousCubic toACCSystemCharges.Charges\n\nnamespace ACCSystem\n\n/-!\n\n## H. The solutions to the full anomaly cancellation conditions\n\nWe define the type `Sols` of solutions to the full ACCs.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The type of solutions to the anomaly cancellation conditions. -/\nstructure Sols (χ : ACCSystem) extends χ.QuadSols where\n  /-- The condition that the charge satisfies the cubic ACC. -/\n  cubicSol : χ.cubicACC val = 0\n\n/-!\n\n### H.1. Extensionality of solutions to the ACCs\n\nWe prove a lemma relating to the equality of two elements of `Sols`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- Two solutions are equal if the underlying charges are equal. -/\nlemma Sols.ext {χ : ACCSystem} {S T : χ.Sols} (h : S.val = T.val) :\n    S = T := by\n  have h := ACCSystemQuad.QuadSols.ext h\n  cases' S\n  simp_all only\n\n/-!\n\n### H.2. The `IsSolution` predicate\n\nwe define a predicate on charges which is true if they correspond to a solution.\n\n-/\n\n/-- A charge `S` is a solution if it extends to a solution. -/\ndef IsSolution (χ : ACCSystem) (S : χ.Charges) : Prop :=\n  ∃ (sol : χ.Sols), sol.val = S\n\n/-!\n\n### H.3. MulAction of `ℚ` on the solutions to the ACCs\n\nLike with `QuadSols`, the type `Sols` does not carry the structure of a module over `ℚ`\nas the cubic nor quadratic ACC is not linear. However it does carry the structure of\na `MulAction` of `ℚ`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- An instance giving the properties and structures to define an action of `ℚ` on `Sols`. -/\ninstance solsMulAction (χ : ACCSystem) : MulAction ℚ χ.Sols where\n  smul a S := ⟨a • S.toQuadSols, by\n    erw [(χ.cubicACC).map_smul, S.cubicSol]\n    exact Rat.mul_zero (a ^ 3)⟩\n  mul_smul a b S := Sols.ext (mul_smul _ _ _)\n  one_smul S := Sols.ext (one_smul _ _)\n\n/-!\n\n### H.4. Embeddings of solutions to the ACCs into quadratic solutions\n\n-/\n\n/-- The inclusion of `Sols` into `QuadSols`. -/\ndef solsInclQuadSols (χ : ACCSystem) : χ.Sols →[ℚ] χ.QuadSols where\n  toFun := Sols.toQuadSols\n  map_smul' _ _ := rfl\n\n@[sorryful]\nlemma solsInclQuadSols_injective (χ : ACCSystem) :\n    Function.Injective χ.solsInclQuadSols := by\n  sorry\n\n/-!\n\n### H.5. Embeddings of solutions to the ACCs into linear solutions\n\n-/\n/-- The inclusion of `Sols` into `LinSols`. -/\ndef solsInclLinSols (χ : ACCSystem) : χ.Sols →[ℚ] χ.LinSols :=\n  MulActionHom.comp χ.quadSolsInclLinSols χ.solsInclQuadSols\n\n@[sorryful]\nlemma solsInclLinSols_injective (χ : ACCSystem) :\n    Function.Injective χ.solsInclLinSols := by\n  sorry",
      "\n  intro S T h_eq\n  have h1 : Function.Injective χ.solsInclQuadSols := by\n    intro S T h\n    simp [solsInclQuadSols] at h ⊢\n    all_goals tauto\n  have h2 : Function.Injective χ.quadSolsInclLinSols := by\n    intro S T h\n    simp [quadSolsInclLinSols] at h ⊢\n    all_goals tauto\n  have h3 : solsInclQuadSols S = solsInclQuadSols T := by\n    simp [solsInclLinSols] at h_eq ⊢\n    all_goals try { tauto }\n    all_goals try { \n      simp_all [solsInclQuadSols, quadSolsInclLinSols]\n      all_goals try { tauto }\n    }\n  exact h1 h3",
      "\n  intro s₁ s₂ h\n  have h1 : (s₁ : χ.Sols).val = (s₂ : χ.Sols).val := by\n    simpa using h\n  have h4 : (s₁ : χ.Sols).toQuadSols = (s₂ : χ.Sols).toQuadSols := by\n    apply χ.solsInclQuadSols_injective\n    simpa using h1\n  have h7 : (s₁ : χ.Sols).toQuadSols = (s₂ : χ.Sols).toQuadSols := h4\n  apply χ.quadSolsInclLinSols_injective\n  simpa using h7",
      "\n  cases' S\n  simp_all only\n\n/-!\n\n## G. The solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations\n\nWe define the type `Sols` of solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The type of solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations. -/\nstructure Sols (χ : ACCSystemBase) extends χ.Sols where\n  /-- The condition that the charge satisfies the cubic equations. -/\n  cubicSol : ∀ i : Fin χ.numberCubic, (χ.cubicEquations i) val = 0\n\n/-!\n\n### G.1. The `IsSolution` predicate\n\nwe define a predicate on charges which is true if they correspond to a solution.\n\n-/\n\n/-- A charge `S` is a solution if it satisfies all linear, quadratic and cubic equations. -/\ndef IsSolution (χ : ACCSystemBase) (S : χ.Charges) : Prop :=\n  ∀ i : Fin (χ.numberLinear + χ.numberQuadratic + χ.numberCubic), (χ.equations i) val = 0\n\n/-!\n\n### G.2. The solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations form an additive commutative group\n\nWe prove that the solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations form an additive commutative group.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations form an additive commutative group. -/\ninstance solsAddCommGroup (χ : ACCSystemBase) : AddCommGroup (χ.Sols) :=\n  Subtype.valAddCommGroup (fun S => S.cubicSol) (by\n    intro S T hST\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hST]\n    exact (χ.cubicEquations i).map_zero\n  ) (by\n    intro S T hST\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hST]\n    exact (χ.cubicEquations i).map_add (S.val) (T.val)\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    exact (χ.cubicEquations i).map_neg (S.val)\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    exact ⟨S.val, fun i => by simp [hS]⟩\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_smul (S.val) i]\n  )\n\n/-!\n\n### G.3. The solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations form a module over `ℚ`\n\nWe prove that the solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations form a module over `ℚ`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations form a module over `ℚ`. -/\ninstance solsModule (χ : ACCSystemBase) : Module ℚ (χ.Sols) :=\n  Subtype.valModule (fun S => S.cubicSol) (by\n    intro S hS a\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_smul]\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS a b\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_add]\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_neg]\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    exact ⟨S.val, fun i => by simp [hS]⟩\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_smul]\n  )\n\n/-!\n\n### G.4. Extensionality of solutions to the linear, quadratic and cubic equations\n\nWe prove a lemma relating to the equality of two elements of `Sols`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- Two solutions are equal if the underlying charges are equal. -/\n@[ext]\nlemma Sols.ext {χ : ACCSystemBase} {S T : χ.Sols} (h : S.val = T.val) : S = T := by\n  cases' S\n  simp_all only\n\n/-!\n\n## H. The solutions to the cubic equations\n\nWe define the type `Sols` of solutions to the cubic equations.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The type of solutions to the cubic equations. -/\nstructure Sols (χ : ACCSystemBase) extends χ.Sols where\n  /-- The condition that the charge satisfies the cubic equations. -/\n  cubicSol : ∀ i : Fin χ.numberCubic, (χ.cubicEquations i) val = 0\n\n/-!\n\n### H.1. The `IsSolution` predicate\n\nwe define a predicate on charges which is true if they correspond to a solution.\n\n-/\n\n/-- A charge `S` is a solution if it satisfies all cubic equations. -/\ndef IsSolution (χ : ACCSystemBase) (S : χ.Charges) : Prop :=\n  ∀ i : Fin χ.numberCubic, (χ.cubicEquations i) val = 0\n\n/-!\n\n### H.2. The solutions to the cubic equations form an additive commutative group\n\nWe prove that the solutions to the cubic equations form an additive commutative group.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The solutions to the cubic equations form an additive commutative group. -/\ninstance solsAddCommGroup (χ : ACCSystemBase) : AddCommGroup (χ.Sols) :=\n  Subtype.valAddCommGroup (fun S => S.cubicSol) (by\n    intro S T hST\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hST]\n    exact (χ.cubicEquations i).map_zero\n  ) (by\n    intro S T hST\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hST]\n    exact (χ.cubicEquations i).map_add (S.val) (T.val)\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    exact (χ.cubicEquations i).map_neg (S.val)\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    exact ⟨S.val, fun i => by simp [hS]⟩\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_smul (S.val) i]\n  )\n\n/-!\n\n### H.3. The solutions to the cubic equations form a module over `ℚ`\n\nWe prove that the solutions to the cubic equations form a module over `ℚ`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The solutions to the cubic equations form a module over `ℚ`. -/\ninstance solsModule (χ : ACCSystemBase) : Module ℚ (χ.Sols) :=\n  Subtype.valModule (fun S => S.cubicSol) (by\n    intro S hS a\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_smul]\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS a b\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_add]\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_neg]\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    exact ⟨S.val, fun i => by simp [hS]⟩\n  ) (by\n    intro S hS\n    simp_all only [Set.mem_setOf_eq]\n    intro i\n    rw [hS]\n    simp [(χ.cubicEquations i).map_smul]\n  )\n\n/-!\n\n### H.4. Extensionality of solutions to the cubic equations\n\nWe prove a lemma relating to the equality of two elements of `Sols`.\n\n-/\n\n/-- Two solutions are equal if the underlying charges are equal. -/\n@[ext]\nlemma Sols.ext {χ : ACCSystemBase} {S T : χ.Sols} (h : S.val = T.val) : S = T := by\n  cases' S\n  simp_all only\n\n/-!\n\n## I. The solutions to the system of equations\n\nWe define the type `Sols` of solutions to the system of equations.\n\n-/\n\n/-- The type of solutions to the system of equations. -/\nstructure Sols (χ : ACCSystemBase) extends χ.Sols where\n  /-- The condition that the charge satisfies all equations. -/\n  allSols : ∀ i : Fin (χ.numberLinear + χ.numberQuadratic +",
